    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** (77.95) and **Kyle Tucker** (76.99). **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive park-factor boost (+16%) and favorable wind conditions against Ed Rodriguez, while **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite start despite a challenging matchup, buoyed by his superior xwOBA and prime spot in the two-hole. **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) and **Josh Lowe** (72.21) also warrant attention; **Josh Lowe** is a particularly strong play today as he draws a +19% SP skill boost against Gil, maximizing his potential for a productive day at the plate.\n\nThe most difficult decision for today's lineup involved the benching of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (59.73). Despite his impressive power profile and strong xwOBA, he was narrowly squeezed out by the optimization model in favor of more efficient platoon and order-based spots. Elsewhere, **Luis Robert Jr.** (41.44) and **Jorge Polanco** (43.25) are active despite suboptimal projections, largely due to the scarcity of high-speed, high-order floor options in our 5x5 format, though both are battling a significant -19% SP skill penalty against Ohtani. \n\nManagers should monitor the status of **Marcell Ozuna** (63.29) closely, as the 37% rain risk in his matchup against Irvin poses a tangible threat to his ability to log a full game. While **Drake Baldwin** and **Nolan Schanuel** are trending upward with scores of 67.65 and 69.16 respectively, the reliance on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions for many of these hitters introduces a layer of variance that could shift these scores once final cards are exchanged. We are banking on the aggressive top-of-order usage for **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** to offset the drag created by the challenging SP matchups facing **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jorge Polanco**.",
